    "careers_h423": "Equity for Everyone",
    "careers_h424": "Annual Team Retreat",
    "careers_h425": "Application",
    "careers_h426": "30-min Intro Call",
    "careers_h427": "Practical Task",
    "careers_h428": "Offer",
    "careers_p29": "At MathMate, every feature you ship helps a student get unstuck. If you want your work to have a direct, visible impact on real people learning real things — this is the team for you.",
    "careers_p30": "We're a small team with a big mission — which means every person genuinely shapes the product.",
    "careers_p31": "Every line of code, every design decision, every word in an explanation reaches a student in a real moment of need. The impact is not abstract — it's in the reviews and the messages we get from users every week.",
    "careers_p32": "We're lean by design. That means less bureaucracy, faster decisions, and real ownership of the things you build. If you've ever wanted to see your ideas go from conversation to shipped feature in a week — this is that environment.",
    "careers_p33": "MathMate is a remote-first team. Work from anywhere — we care about what you ship, not where you sit. Meetings are purposeful and async communication is the default.",
    "careers_p34": "We build a learning product, so it would be strange if we didn't value our own learning. Every team member gets a personal development budget, book allowance, and access to courses — no approval process required.",
    "careers_p35": "Everyone who joins MathMate gets equity. We believe the people who build the product should share in what it becomes. We'll walk you through the details transparently during the offer process.",
    "careers_p36": "We hire people we trust and then trust the people we hire. No pointless status meetings, no micromanagement, no politics. If you want to change how something works, raise it — and watch it happen.",
    "careers_p37": "We hire for craft, curiosity, and care — not just credentials.",
    "careers_p38": "We hire opportunistically for exceptional people. If you believe you'd make MathMate better, send us a note at <a href=\"mailto:hello@mathmate.app\" style=\"color:#8B5CF6;text-decoration:none\">hello@mathmate.app</a> with a short intro and what you'd work on.",
    "careers_p39": "Practical benefits that reflect what we actually care about — not a list of foosball tables.",
    "careers_p40": "We were remote from day one. There's no office we're going back to. Async is the norm, not the exception.",
    "careers_p41": "Annual personal development budget for courses, books, conferences, or anything that makes you better at your craft.",
    "careers_p42": "Comprehensive health insurance for all full-time team members and their dependants, wherever they're based.",
    "careers_p43": "Work when you're most productive. Core hours exist for collaboration, but we're not watching the clock.",
    "careers_p44": "£800 / $1,000 home office budget when you join — laptop, monitor, chair, whatever you need to do your best work.",
    "careers_p45": "28 days PTO (plus local public holidays) for full-time staff. We actively encourage people to actually take it.",
    "careers_p46": "All full-time roles include meaningful equity. We want you to share in what we're building — transparently and fairly.",
    "careers_p47": "Once a year, the whole team meets somewhere in the world for a week of collaboration, strategy, and time together as humans.",
    "careers_p48": "Respectful of your time. No surprise rounds. No trick questions. We move fast.",
    "careers_p49": "Send your CV and a short note on why MathMate. No cover letter templates, please — genuine is better.",
    "careers_p50": "A conversation with a team member — not a screener. We want to understand you, not test you.",
    "careers_p51": "A short, paid task relevant to the role. We pay for your time. The task reflects real work — no abstract puzzles.",
    "careers_p52": "If it's a fit for both sides, we move to offer. Full transparency on equity, comp, and what joining actually looks like.",
    "careers_p53": "Browse the open roles above or send a speculative application — we'd love to hear from you.",
