    "topics_h325": "Number Theory   Discrete Math",
    "topics_p26": "MathMate covers the full K-12 mathematics curriculum — from counting and fractions to calculus and linear algebra — with concept-by-concept learning that builds real understanding.",
    "topics_p27": "Understanding how numbers are built, from ones and tens to millions, and how digits change meaning based on position.",
    "topics_p28": "Core arithmetic operations with whole numbers, including carrying and borrowing across place values.",
    "topics_p29": "Times tables, long multiplication, and division with and without remainders — built to make these feel natural, not memorised.",
    "topics_p30": "From understanding what a fraction means to adding, subtracting, multiplying, and dividing them with full step-by-step reasoning.",
    "topics_p31": "Converting between fractions, decimals, and percentages, plus real-world applications like discounts and interest.",
    "topics_p32": "Length, weight, time, volume, and temperature — plus converting between metric and imperial units confidently.",
    "topics_p33": "Understanding relationships between quantities — from unit rates to scale drawings to direct and inverse proportion.",
    "topics_p34": "Expanding the number line below zero — adding, subtracting, multiplying, and dividing with negative numbers.",
    "topics_p35": "Variables, expressions, equations, and inequalities — the foundation of all advanced math, taught one concept at a time.",
    "topics_p36": "Angles, triangles, quadrilaterals, circles, and the Pythagorean theorem — understanding shape properties with proof.",
    "topics_p37": "Mean, median, mode, range — plus reading and drawing bar charts, histograms, scatter plots, and box plots.",
    "topics_p38": "From coin flips to compound events — expressing likelihood, using tree diagrams, and understanding expected outcomes.",
    "topics_p39": "Linear equations, systems of equations, quadratics, polynomials, rational expressions, and function notation.",
    "topics_p40": "Proofs, congruence, similarity, transformations, coordinate geometry, volume, and surface area of 3D shapes.",
    "topics_p41": "Domain, range, function notation, linear/quadratic/exponential/logarithmic functions and their transformations.",
    "topics_p42": "Sin, cos, tan, the unit circle, trigonometric identities, graphs of trig functions, and solving trig equations.",
    "topics_p43": "Arithmetic and geometric sequences, sigma notation, convergence and divergence of infinite series.",
    "topics_p44": "Normal distribution, z-scores, confidence intervals, hypothesis testing, correlation, and regression analysis.",
    "topics_p45": "The foundations of calculus — understanding what a limit is, how to evaluate them, and what continuity means for a function.",
    "topics_p46": "Derivatives from first principles, chain rule, product rule, quotient rule, implicit differentiation, and related rates.",
    "topics_p47": "Antiderivatives, definite integrals, the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus, integration by substitution and by parts.",
    "topics_p48": "Vectors, matrices, systems of linear equations, determinants, eigenvalues and eigenvectors.",
    "topics_p49": "First and second order ODEs, separable equations, linear equations with constant coefficients, and applications.",
    "topics_p50": "Primes, GCD, modular arithmetic, combinatorics, permutations, combinations, and the Binomial Theorem.",
    "topics_p51": "MathMate identifies exactly where to start and guides you through each topic — one concept at a time.",
    "practice_h10": "Sample Problems<br><em>With Full Explanations</em>",
    "practice_h21": "Hundreds More Problems<br><span>In MathMate</span>",
    "practice_p2": "Browse practice problems across topics and difficulty levels. Each one includes a hint and step-by-step method — so you learn the approach, not just the answer.",
    "practice_p3": "These are just samples. The app has unlimited practice problems per topic — all with full step-by-step explanations, personalised to your level.",
    "press_h10": "Everything You Need<br>to <em>Write About MathMate.</em>",
